# Backend Services

- Read the service `README.md`, `ARCHITECTURE.md`, and `TESTING.md` before changing service behavior.
- `services/backend` owns MCP registration, OAuth/token state, user skills, and audit events today.
- `services/backend-facade` is the app-facing API surface; it forwards to backend services and must not import their Python modules.
- Keep `/internal/v1/*` off the facade unless an accepted spec updates the service boundary.
- Do not add sibling services to `PYTHONPATH` or reuse another service's `.venv`.
- Update `packages/api-types` and facade/product API docs when app-facing payloads or routes change.
